From: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2015 20:41:31 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 0309/1168] drm/radeon: do a posting read in r600_set_irq

commit 9d1393f23d5656cdd5f368efd60694d4aeed81d3 upstream.

To make sure the writes go through the pci bridge.

bug:
https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=90741

Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Stefan Guendhoer <stefan@guendhoer.com>

Former-commit-id: 3af33968e5270606c39c7fa4849e406342715eeb
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r600.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r600.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r600.c
index 4cf21ec..90b0075 100755
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r600.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r600.c
@@ -3459,6 +3459,9 @@ int r600_init(struct radeon_device *rdev)
 		rdev->accel_working = false;
 	}
 
+	/* posting read */
+	RREG32(R_000E50_SRBM_STATUS);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
